An initiative called Project 20 Million has disclosed its readiness to register 20 million Nigerians in the quest to salvage the  country from alleged lackluster leadership. This was contained in a statement signed by the director-general,  Ikechukwu Chukwunyere and director of Administration, Tijani Ali  Danjuma at a press conference held in Abuja, where the Coalition of  Civil Society Organisations In Nigeria (COCSON), Democratic Youth  Magazine, Advocates of the Not-Too-Young-To-Run Bill, journalists,  students and other major stakeholders explained that the essence of  the registration is to influence the process of decision making,  ensuring accountable leadership and enthronement of good governance. They also said that it has become necessary to initiate Project 20 Million, “So that only credible people and persons with great  managerial experience can take up the responsibility of salvaging  Nigeria from lackluster leadership.”